00:11:03.238 --> 00:11:05.530 align:middle line:84%
I think that's one of the
really most striking and most

00:11:05.530 --> 00:11:07.920 align:middle line:84%
inspirational features
about knowing you,

00:11:07.920 --> 00:11:09.700 align:middle line:84%
and about being able
to take care of you,

00:11:09.700 --> 00:11:12.850 align:middle line:84%
is that you really pushed
the envelope beyond what

00:11:12.850 --> 00:11:14.500 align:middle line:90%
I think most people can do.

00:11:14.500 --> 00:11:16.390 align:middle line:84%
And I think if we
could just understand

00:11:16.390 --> 00:11:19.120 align:middle line:84%
it a little bit better, and
bottle that up, and give

00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:21.170 align:middle line:84%
that to some of
my other patients,

00:11:21.170 --> 00:11:23.360 align:middle line:84%
I think we'll be able
to help a lot of people.

00:11:23.360 --> 00:11:25.720 align:middle line:84%
And I think you really serve
as an inspiration on how

00:11:25.720 --> 00:11:27.640 align:middle line:90%
you can work through loss.

00:11:27.640 --> 00:11:29.240 align:middle line:84%
And the role of
resilience in that,

00:11:29.240 --> 00:11:34.570 align:middle line:84%
meaning, basically, if you're
down, you pick yourself up.

00:11:34.570 --> 00:11:36.500 align:middle line:90%
And you push yourself forward.

00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:40.500 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

